<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870811-0095 </DOCNO><HL> Gencorp Unit WinsAir Force ContractFor $432.8 Million</HL><DD> 08/11/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> GQ RD SC ROK LOR GYAEROSPACE (ARO)DEFENSE DEPARTMENT (DEF) </IN><DATELINE> WASHINGTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Aerojet Electrosystems Co., a unit of Gencorp Inc., won a $432.8 million Air Force contract for infrared sensors to equip five early-warning satellites.    The award includes support to launch the satellites, which are designed to detect missile launches from the Soviet Union. Work is to be completed in September 1993.    In other awards yesterday, Loral Corp. got a $126 million Air Force contract for electronic equipment for aircraft.    ITT Felec Services Inc. received a $90.9 million Air Force contract to operate radars.    Rockwell International Corp. was issued a $30.1 million Navy contract for shipboard navigation equipment.    The Defense Logistics Agency awarded Carbon Hill Manufacturing Co. and Vanco Industries Inc. contracts of $14.4 million and $10.5 million, respectively, for coats.    Shell Oil Co., a unit of Royal Dutch/Shell Group, got a $14.3 million Defense Logistics Agency contract for naval distillates, and Coastal Eagle Point Oil Co. got a $12.2 million contract for naval distillates.    Greenbrier Industries Inc. was awarded a $13.9 million Defense Logistics Agency contract for coveralls.    Grumman Corp. received a $10.7 million Navy contract for E-2C aircraft production. </TEXT></DOC>